communicated by:
ProMED

[The above reports summarize the situation as of late December 2022, concerning the fungal meningitis outbreak in Durango, Mexico. As of 10 Dec 2022, a total of 1787 people had undergone surgical procedures and received epidural anesthesia since May 2022 at 4 private hospitals in Durango. As of 26 Dec 2022, a total of 77 cases of meningitis, 74 women and 3 men, were reported among the patients who underwent surgery and epidural anesthesia in Durango, including 29 deaths related to this outbreak. The fungus _Fusarium solani_ was identified in the cases.

_Fusarium solani_, a species complex of at least 26 closely related filamentous fungi, is a common soil fungus that is implicated in plant disease, as well as human disease, notably of the cornea and endophthalmitis, disseminated disease, osteomyelitis, skin infection, and fungemia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fusarium_solani).

Fungal contamination of the anesthetic drug that was used during an epidural procedure was suspected. Authorities quarantined various formulations of bupivacaine used in epidural anesthesia, as well as morphine, all made by the same laboratory, but _Fusarium solani_ was reported not to have been detected in the analyzed drug samples. Bupivacaine, often in combination with morphine, is an anesthetic used in epidural nerve blocks during or after surgery or other procedures, such as childbirth (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bupivacaine). We await more information as the outbreak investigation unfolds.

Fungal contamination of a drug administered epidurally caused the large, multistate invasive fungal infection outbreak associated with contaminated methylprednisolone injections in the United States in late 2012 and 2013 (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4669562/) and another fungal meningitis outbreak in the United States in 2002 (ProMED post Fungal meningitis, contaminated drug - USA (03) 20021212.6046).

Durango City (population 654 876 in 2015) is the capital and largest city of the Mexican state of Durango, located in northwestern Mexico (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durango_City). - Mod.ML

